  "prompt": "What is the average number of followers per user on Instagram",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram doesn't release an official average number of followers per user. However, various third-party analyses and studies have been conducted over the years. Keep in mind that these numbers can vary widely and change over time due to the platform's growth and evolving user behaviors.\n\nA study from 2021 suggested that the median number of followers for an Instagram account was around 150. This means half of Instagram users had fewer than 150 followers, and half had more. However, averages can be skewed by accounts with extremely high follower counts, so the median is often a more useful measure for understanding the typical user's experience.\n\nFor the most current statistics, it's best to look at recent studies or analyses from reputable sources in social media marketing and analytics.",
